-- FINMA in contact with UBS in rogue trader case
-- 
-- Thu Sep 15, 2011 4:44am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/09/15/us-ubs-finma-idUSTRE78E1GD20110915

 

 ZURICH  (Reuters) - Switzerland's financial markets regulator FINMA is in close contact with Swiss bank UBS after the bank discovered unauthorized trading by a trader in its investment bank had caused a loss of some $2 billion. 

 "UBS immediately informed us. We have taken note of the case and we are in close contact with the bank," a spokesman for FINMA said. (Reporting by Oliver Hirt)